<abstract label="Abstract">The Loudoun Restoration and Preservation Society  (LRPS) was founded in 1967 to promote the recognition, restoration, and preservation of historical sites and buildings in Loudoun County.  LRPS merged with the Preservation Society of Loudoun County in 2008.  The collection contains minutes, the charter and by-laws for the society, lists of officers and board members, correspondence, legal and financial documents, as well as materials relating to August Court Days, restoration projects, and the 100th anniversary of celebration of the Leesburg courthouse. 
</abstract>
